PN,44705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1775927152
OL,3,CPolice investigating cyber attack on
OL,4,CNI school IT systems
OL,6,FIn July 2025, an Audit Office report
OL,7,Fwarned that 'delays in delivering
OL,8,Fmajor public sector IT projects were
OL,9,Fresulting in existing contracts for
OL,10,Flegacy systems' such as C2K - which
OL,11,Fwas first established in 1998 - 'being
OL,12,Frepeatedly extended at a cost of
OL,13,Fhundreds of millions of pounds to
OL,14,Ftaxpayers.'
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1775927152
OL,3,CPolice investigating cyber attack on
OL,4,CNI school IT systems
OL,6,FIn the same report the auditor general
OL,7,FDorinnia Carville also noted that
OL,8,Fthere can be valid reasons for
OL,9,Fextending contracts, but that in many
OL,10,Fcases these extensions were not a
OL,11,Fstrategically planned choice but
OL,12,Frather made out of a necessity to
OL,13,Fmaintain continuity of service.
OL,15,F"Extensions come at a cost, including
OL,16,Fmissed opportunities to improve
OL,17,Fefficiency, functionality and
OL,18,Fperformance, as well as risks of
OL,19,Fservice disruption or vulnerability to
OL,20,Fcyber attacks,'" she said.
OL,26,@wD@AOU|D@PO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/8
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1775927152
OL,3,CPolice investigating cyber attack on
OL,4,CNI school IT systems
OL,6,F"Additionally, there are significant
OL,7,Ffinancial costs ` the report looks in
OL,8,Fdetail at five projects which each
OL,9,Fexperienced delays or issues, with
OL,10,Fsubsequent contract extension costs
OL,11,Ftotaling in excess of #573 million."
OL,13,FWe have asked the Education Authority
OL,14,Ffor an interview but have been told no
OL,15,Fone is available.
OL,17,FWe have also asked for a fresh
OL,18,Fstatement today around the Audit
OL,19,FOffice report but were directed to a
OL,20,Fprevious statement advising schools to
OL,21,Freset their passwords.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@dO]
